Short Info about UTC vs. Prague Time

UTC (Coordinated Universal Time) is the primary time standard by which the world regulates clocks and time.
Prague usually observes Central European Time (CET), which is UTC+1 in winter and UTC+2 (Central European Summer Time, CEST) during daylight saving time.
So, depending on the time of the year:

Winter: Prague is 1 hour ahead of UTC.
Summer: Prague is 2 hours ahead of UTC.